history.text: Hi, Sounds like an interesting movie with DiCaprio getting secrets from victims' dreams. What do you think?
It got a pretty good rating on Rotten Tomatoes - 86%.
DiCaprio does a great job with the love story!
I'm not usually a fan of science fiction, but this one sounds like I might like it even not liking that genre.  Have you seen it?
This is very interesting too that an architect is the one in charge of "constructing" the various dreamscapes. I want to see it after reading about it.
The plot does seem intriguing with dream worlds and stuff.
I usually like Joseph Gordon-Levitt now that he has grown up.  And DiCaprio is sometimes pretty good as well.
Yes, the actors have quite interesting roles especially DiCaprio as a thief in this way
I don't know if I've seen any other movies directed by Christopher Nolan.
The espionage with technology is cool
Wow, the level of the dreams and shared dream is a strange concept.
And the use of "kicks" seems like a recipe for disaster.
The subconscious as well gives it an interesting loop.
Saito ending up in limbo does not sound like a fun time.  Such a complicated world, or dreams...
Being in limbo is a scary concept too.
And it sounds like an interesting concept to have armed projections in your head to protect you against this type of thing.
Would be interesting to have someone in another person's dreams.  It's unchartered territory.
Funny to see the military technology to get into the dream world.  Scary concept too.
DiCaprio as usual did a fantastic job in the movie.
But at least it sounds like there is a way to protect yourself from it.
Interesting that you can spend so much time in a dream world but in reality it isn't that long.  Sounds like it can really mess with you mind.  Mal committing suicide sounds like a downer.
It's nice Cobb has a partner who helps out
I don't understand how multiple people can get into the same dream and interact with each other.
That's a strange concept that can be developed in this movie with DiCaprio's acting.
Cobb revealing he went into Limbo is scary to feel like 50 years passes in a few hours.
Exciting that totem can be used to distinguish the dreams from a reality.
But it sounds like the totem idea isn't foolproof.  Mal didn't believe it and it sounds like Cobb doesn't in the end either.
Cobbs resolves his guilt which helps the plot, though.
But I don't understand his guilt.  Just that maybe he should have left her in the dream?
Mal still thought she was dreaming when she woke up though
It isn't his fault that she couldn't tell the difference between dream and reality - unless he kind of made her join him.
She framed Cobb so that was difficult for him.
